- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper discusses the efficiency of the software development process through simulation results. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper involves modeling and simulating a growing process of a project. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is another possible category as the paper touches on the social aspect of the open source software community. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper involves developing a simulation model for the growing process of a project.
